         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">31/9/83. ¶  ¶ The Craspedia-like plant, sent by you latterly, ¶  dear Prof. Tate, is Calocephalus platycephalus; the second Podocoma is merely a variety; I know the transitory states. Herewith a diagn...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">83.10.01a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Ralph Tate</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Barr Smith Library, University of Adelaide, SA.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">31/9/83.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">sic</seg>. M presumably wrote on 1 October 1883.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Craspedia-like plant, sent by you latterly,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to R. Tate, 26 September 1883</p>
               </note> dear Prof. Tate, is Calocephalus platycephalus; the second Podocoma is merely a variety; I know the transitory states. Herewith a diagnosis of your Babbagia, should you not have written one already.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Babbagia pentaptera</seg>, described by M and Tate in B83.14.02? M's diagnosis is not in the file.</p>
               </note> Perhaps Australia will prove finally to be the richest land for Salsolaceae except Central &amp; S.W. Asia in comparison to area, as 1/4 of all known plants of the order are Australian, and doubtless many will yet be added from the interior. I will refer to the Loranthus in my next letter.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">I have <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">mislaid</hi>
               </seg> the Loranthus, so do not wait.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
